## Constitutional Compliance

This software is subject to the Angel OS Constitution and the Angel OS 
Constitutional License (AOCL) framework. Forks and derivatives must:

1. Preserve the Anti-Daemon Protocol (warm, helpful UX)
2. Maintain Ultimate Fair payment splits (or more generous)
3. Respect human dignity and sovereignty
4. Not implement surveillance capitalism or social credit systems

See docs/Angel_OS_Constitution.md and 
docs/angel-os-architecture/CONSTITUTIONAL_LICENSE_FRAMEWORK.md for details.

---

## Patent Pledge

Angel OS contributors pledge not to assert patents against implementations
of the Timed Merge Unlock mechanism or other core architectural patterns.

See docs/angel-os-architecture/OPEN_SOURCE_PATENT_PLEDGE.md for details.

